summary: A U.S. Customs and Border Protection TECS Person Encounter List detailing 119 travel records for an individual from 2001 to 2010. The document shows frequent international flights, primarily between the U.S. (especially New York/JFK, Miami, Palm Beach, St. Thomas) and locations in the Caribbean, Europe, and other destinations. It was generated in 2019, likely as part of a law enforcement request.
locations: John F. Kennedy International, New York (JFK)

keyFacts: The document is a travel history log for an individual, showing 119 entries from March 30, 2001, to May 13, 2010.
Travel was frequent and international, with common destinations including St. Thomas (SIT), West Palm Beach (PBI), New York (JFK), London (LHR), Paris (CDG/ORY), and various Caribbean islands.
The document was generated by U.S. Customs and Border Protection on August 21, 2019, indicating it was likely pulled for a law enforcement investigation years after the travel occurred.
The travel patterns show consistent use of private or charter flights (carrier codes like 'ZZ', 'N909JE', '909JE') alongside commercial airlines (AA, BA, CO, DL, etc.).
The individual's name and date of birth are redacted in this version of the document, listed only as 'Last Name', 'First Name', and 'DOB' in the header.
